    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
          <p rend="indent(7)"><add>Yiddish</add></p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">My Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p><add>Yiddish</add></p>
			<p><persName role="author">A Rice</persName></p>
			<p>.<date>July</date> <add>Yiddish</add></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><addressee>Rev. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p><hi rend="underline">post paid</hi> in <placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><add><hi rend="underline">Yiddish</hi></add></p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>&#44; <date>Monday</date></p>
          <p rend="indent(10)"><date>13<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Sivan &#40;May&#41;&#44; 1850</date>.</p>
			<p>My dear Sir&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Be so good as to advertise in<lb/> the next number of the &#8220;Occident&#44;&#8221;<lb/> the notice written below&#44; and after&#45;<lb/>wards&#44; send me a bill for it&#44; and<lb/> the congregation will pay for it. I<lb/> shall write it here in German and<lb/> you will translate it correctly<lb/> into the English Language.</p>
			<p>&#8220;The congregation of <placeName>Baltimore</placeName> de&#45;<lb/>sires to have a person who will be<lb/> able to fill completely the position<lb/> as cantor and&#44; at the same time&#44;<lb/> as teacher of Hebrew in a school<lb/> of 60 children. He must be quite<lb/> accomplished as cantor and<lb/> teacher. His salary will be &#36;500.<lb/> annually. The year begins the</p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p><date>first of next October</date>. No one<lb/> should present himself unless<lb/> he is able to do well in both of<lb/> these respects. All applications<lb/> must arrive post free&#44; otherwise<lb/> they will not be accepted. They<lb/> are to be addressed to me until<lb/> the <date>first of August</date>&#44; as follows&#58;<lb/> <persName role="author">Rev. A. Rice</persName>&#44; <placeName>North Exeter&#44; no.<lb/> 8</placeName>. The person who is considered<lb/> fit will receive an answer<lb/> and will have to present himself<lb/> here at his own expense. He will<lb/> then be interviewed by the congrega&#45;<lb/>tion.&#8221;</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)">I am and shall always</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)">remain&#44; Most respectfully&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(7)"> Your friend&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">A. Rice</persName></p>
			<p>You will include<lb/> this only in your<lb/> <date>July</date> number.</p>
          
        </body>
